<li id="cite_note-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10" title="">^</a></b> Sycamore Gap, a section of the wall between two crests just west of Milecastle 38, is locally known as the "Robin Hood Tree" for its use in the 1991 film <i><a href="/wiki/Robin_Hood:_Prince_of_Thieves" title="Robin Hood: Prince of Thieves">Robin Hood: Prince of Thieves</a></i> (1991).</li>
</ol>
</div>
